data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
California is having a moment, and with that comes greater scrutiny. The presidential campaign is a fight to define both the state and Kamala Harris for the rest of America.

The annual East L.A. Classic football game draws the biggest crows in the City Section, including 22,000 at the Coliseum in 2022.

Federal prosecutors allege Jasveen Sangha, one of five people charged in actor Matthew Perrys death, was known by another name: Ketamine Queen.

From the Middle East to Latin America, incidents of water-related violence have been rising. New data from the Pacific Institute show 2023 was a record year.

Langers deli owner Norm Langer said hes tired of cajoling city officials to clean the streets, restore public safety and make MacArthur Park a destination again.

DeShaun Foster knows there are plenty of people who dont think he should be coaching UCLA football. Hes out to have the final say on the matter.

Mexicos judges walked off the job following President Andres Manuel Lpez Obradors plan to overhaul the judiciary, with judges elected not appointed.
